## Example 2 
::: {.callout-tip}
## Example
Solve $$y'''+y''=\sec^2 x$$

::: {.callout-caution collapse="true"}
## Solution:

`STEP 1:` 

$$r^3+r^2=0\rightarrow r^2(r+1)=0\rightarrow r_{1,2,3}=\{0,0,-1\}$$

$$\Rightarrow y_c = c_1+c_2x+c_3e^{-x}$$

`STEP 2:` 

$$y_p=v_1+v_2x+v_3e^{-x}$$

`STEP 3:` 

$$v_1'+v_2'x+v_3'e^{-x}=0$$
$$v_1'\cdot 0+v_2'\cdot 1+v_3'(-e^{-x})=0$$
$$v_3'e^{-x}=\sec^2 x$$

`STEP 4:`

$$\boxed{v_3'=e^x\sec^2 x}$$
$$\Rightarrow v_2'=e^{-x}v_3'=e^{-x}\cdot e^x\sec^2 x= \sec^2 x$$
$$\boxed{v_2'=\sec^2 x}$$

$$\Rightarrow v_1'=-v_2'x-v_3'e^{-x}=-x\sec^2 x-e^x\sec^2 xe^{-x}=-\sec^2 x(x+1)$$

$$\boxed{v_1'=-\sec^2 x(x+1)}$$
